WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:09.551 --> 00:00:11.386 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
In Paris and Milan,

00:00:11.469 --> 00:00:14.931 position:50% align:center
many brands hold open auditions
for their Fashion Week shows.

00:00:15.015 --> 00:00:17.225 position:50% align:center
Anybody can try out.

00:00:18.101 --> 00:00:20.353 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI] If they want,
a designer might even pick

00:00:20.437 --> 00:00:23.314 position:50% align:center
a total novice to strut
for them on the runway.

00:00:23.398 --> 00:00:25.900 position:50% align:center
All you need is a good figure.

00:00:25.984 --> 00:00:29.279 position:50% align:center
Of course, that includes height.

00:00:29.362 --> 00:00:30.530 position:50% align:center
When it's your turn,

00:00:30.613 --> 00:00:32.615 position:50% align:center
they have you walk in
front of the designer.

00:00:32.699 --> 00:00:35.326 position:50% align:center
Usually for about ten meters.

00:00:35.410 --> 00:00:37.704 position:50% align:center
I went to dozens of open calls.

00:00:37.787 --> 00:00:39.205 position:50% align:center
Forget ten meters.

00:00:39.289 --> 00:00:41.750 position:50% align:center
None of them let me
walk two steps.

00:00:41.833 --> 00:00:47.881 position:50% align:center
[speaking French]

00:00:49.049 --> 00:00:51.509 position:50% align:center
"Oh, my goodness,
if you're a model,

00:00:51.593 --> 00:00:55.180 position:50% align:center
then an elementary schooler
could be a top model in France."

00:00:55.263 --> 00:00:57.349 position:50% align:center
Wow.

00:00:57.432 --> 00:00:58.933 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:00:59.017 --> 00:01:00.602 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
Guess there's just no demand for

00:01:00.685 --> 00:01:03.480 position:50% align:center
"new model on the scene,
Chiyuki Fujito."

00:01:03.563 --> 00:01:04.689 position:50% align:center
None.

00:01:04.773 --> 00:01:05.690 position:50% align:center
[CAMERAMAN A]
You're ruining the balance.

00:01:05.774 --> 00:01:06.900 position:50% align:center
Could you go ahead and step out?

00:01:06.983 --> 00:01:07.776 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
A shooting crew.

00:01:07.859 --> 00:01:09.778 position:50% align:center
You can't go to Paris...

00:01:09.861 --> 00:01:11.446 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
My own dad.

00:01:11.529 --> 00:01:13.782 position:50% align:center
Even the one I admire most.

00:01:13.865 --> 00:01:15.992 position:50% align:center
They've all given up on me.

00:01:16.076 --> 00:01:17.994 position:50% align:center
So then, why?

00:01:18.078 --> 00:01:20.705 position:50% align:center
Why do you always
show up like this?

00:01:20.789 --> 00:01:22.957 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO]
Miss Chiyuki!

00:01:23.041 --> 00:01:25.669 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI] Right when
I'm needing you the most.

00:01:25.752 --> 00:01:29.673 position:50% align:center
How would you feel about
modeling in my show?

00:01:29.756 --> 00:01:34.302 position:50% align:center
Jeez. Way to twist my arm.

00:01:34.386 --> 00:01:36.221 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
How do you do it?

00:01:36.304 --> 00:01:41.685 position:50% align:center
I don't get why, but your
words always save me.

00:01:41.768 --> 00:01:44.312 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO gasps]
Are you okay?

00:01:44.396 --> 00:01:46.398 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
Man, what is it with you?

00:01:46.481 --> 00:01:49.442 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI sniffs]
You throw me off.

00:01:50.443 --> 00:01:53.029 position:50% align:center
Do you mind if I sit
next to you for a while?

00:01:53.113 --> 00:01:54.739 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
Yes.

00:02:03.248 --> 00:02:05.417 position:50% align:center
When I went to Paris,

00:02:05.500 --> 00:02:07.460 position:50% align:center
I knew that it was a long shot,

00:02:07.544 --> 00:02:10.672 position:50% align:center
so it seems silly
to let it get to me.

00:02:10.755 --> 00:02:14.009 position:50% align:center
But I met this amazing
model a little while back.

00:02:14.092 --> 00:02:19.472 position:50% align:center
Her aura was incredible, but she
didn't even want to be a model.

00:02:19.556 --> 00:02:21.766 position:50% align:center
I was so jealous.

00:02:21.850 --> 00:02:25.770 position:50% align:center
I think I've been dragging
that around with me ever since.

00:02:27.814 --> 00:02:28.606 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
What?

00:02:28.690 --> 00:02:30.942 position:50% align:center
It's just... kind of a first.

00:02:31.026 --> 00:02:32.360 position:50% align:center
I've never heard you complain.

00:02:32.444 --> 00:02:34.863 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Well, never again!

00:02:34.946 --> 00:02:38.158 position:50% align:center
What? I didn't mean
anything weird by it!

00:02:39.284 --> 00:02:41.828 position:50% align:center
Honestly, it adds to your charm.

00:02:43.955 --> 00:02:45.582 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO]
Why?!

00:02:51.004 --> 00:02:52.255 position:50% align:center
[KANAMI]
Hey, Toh?

00:02:52.339 --> 00:02:55.633 position:50% align:center
I got the materials.
We're all set for the final.

00:02:55.717 --> 00:02:57.635 position:50% align:center
Very good.

00:02:57.719 --> 00:03:01.056 position:50% align:center
Right then.
Let's get started.

00:04:31.521 --> 00:04:35.692 position:50% align:center
[bell ringing]

00:04:35.775 --> 00:04:39.446 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO] So this is the timeline
leading up to the show.

00:04:39.529 --> 00:04:42.949 position:50% align:center
For my theme,
I'm going with "Wind."

00:04:43.033 --> 00:04:44.701 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
How does that relate to "wa"?

00:04:44.784 --> 00:04:47.579 position:50% align:center
I admit, it's a
pretty abstract idea.

00:04:47.662 --> 00:04:49.956 position:50% align:center
But as long as there's any
connection, it's allowed.

00:04:50.040 --> 00:04:52.292 position:50% align:center
Oh.

00:04:52.375 --> 00:04:55.587 position:50% align:center
So you're going to make
a total of ten outfits, huh?

00:04:55.670 --> 00:04:57.213 position:50% align:center
Just to clarify,

00:04:57.297 --> 00:04:58.840 position:50% align:center
this being an
actual show and all,

00:04:58.923 --> 00:05:02.427 position:50% align:center
I can't be the
only model you use.

00:05:02.510 --> 00:05:04.637 position:50% align:center
How are you handling that?

00:05:04.721 --> 00:05:06.348 position:50% align:center
The others?

00:05:08.183 --> 00:05:09.809 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO]
Ya know, you're the one who

00:05:09.893 --> 00:05:12.395 position:50% align:center
inspired me to choose
"wind" as my theme.

00:05:12.479 --> 00:05:13.646 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI grunts]

00:05:13.730 --> 00:05:15.065 position:50% align:center
With typhoons,

00:05:15.148 --> 00:05:17.901 position:50% align:center
the lower the atmospheric
pressure is in the center,

00:05:17.984 --> 00:05:20.653 position:50% align:center
the stronger the wind blows.

00:05:20.737 --> 00:05:22.072 position:50% align:center
Wait, "lower"?

00:05:22.155 --> 00:05:23.782 position:50% align:center
Is that a reference
to my height?!

00:05:23.865 --> 00:05:25.700 position:50% align:center
Please, just listen!

00:05:25.784 --> 00:05:27.160 position:50% align:center
You're relentless
like a typhoon

00:05:27.243 --> 00:05:29.329 position:50% align:center
despite what anyone
else says about you.

00:05:29.412 --> 00:05:30.955 position:50% align:center
But you're also quick
to support others

00:05:31.039 --> 00:05:32.290 position:50% align:center
like a wind at their back,

00:05:32.374 --> 00:05:34.834 position:50% align:center
with all the comfort
of a warm breeze.

00:05:34.918 --> 00:05:38.922 position:50% align:center
Right? Doesn't that
sound just like you?

00:05:39.005 --> 00:05:41.841 position:50% align:center
You're the star of
my show, Miss Chiyuki.

00:05:43.009 --> 00:05:45.136 position:50% align:center
I'd love your opinion on it.

00:05:45.220 --> 00:05:47.430 position:50% align:center
Feel free to let it rip!

00:05:50.558 --> 00:05:53.436 position:50% align:center
First, use top-notch
models, 'kay?

00:05:53.520 --> 00:05:55.271 position:50% align:center
So I can outshine them.

00:05:55.355 --> 00:05:56.731 position:50% align:center
Will do!

00:05:56.815 --> 00:05:59.359 position:50% align:center
By the way, I'm already
finished with the toile mockups.

00:05:59.442 --> 00:06:01.152 position:50% align:center
Do you feel like trying them on?

00:06:01.236 --> 00:06:02.320 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
Sure, why not.

00:06:02.404 --> 00:06:05.949 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO]
I'll be back in a sec.

00:06:06.032 --> 00:06:09.119 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
Right, I'll have to thank him.

00:06:09.202 --> 00:06:13.748 position:50% align:center
After all, he sure knows how
to make a girl feel important.

00:06:16.167 --> 00:06:19.462 position:50% align:center
Wait, you do realize
this thing doesn't fit?

00:06:19.546 --> 00:06:21.798 position:50% align:center
Or do I need to remind you
that this is what happens

00:06:21.881 --> 00:06:23.091 position:50% align:center
when you don't
take measurements?

00:06:23.174 --> 00:06:24.592 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO]
I know that!

00:06:24.676 --> 00:06:27.595 position:50% align:center
But I didn't wanna make
things awkward, so...

00:06:27.679 --> 00:06:29.681 position:50% align:center
[gasping]

00:06:30.515 --> 00:06:34.144 position:50% align:center
[heart pounding]

00:06:34.227 --> 00:06:36.021 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
You silly nerd.

00:06:36.104 --> 00:06:39.190 position:50% align:center
You asked me to help you
and I said I'd do you a favor.

00:06:39.274 --> 00:06:40.734 position:50% align:center
Didn't I?

00:06:40.817 --> 00:06:42.068 position:50% align:center
C'mon, take my measurements!

00:06:42.152 --> 00:06:43.570 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
So, let me get to work!

00:06:43.653 --> 00:06:46.072 position:50% align:center
If you wanna go pro, you need
to get used to this stuff!

00:06:46.156 --> 00:06:51.369 position:50% align:center
AH! Okay, okay. Jeez.
Stripping down out of nowhere!

00:06:51.453 --> 00:06:53.997 position:50% align:center
Do you think you could
at least turn around?

00:06:57.083 --> 00:07:00.879 position:50% align:center
Don't get too excited.
You might have high hopes for me

00:07:00.962 --> 00:07:04.466 position:50% align:center
but there's a chance
I won't measure up.

00:07:09.637 --> 00:07:10.555 position:50% align:center
I'm stepping out.

00:07:10.638 --> 00:07:11.973 position:50% align:center
[KOKORO]
Hm?

00:07:12.057 --> 00:07:13.767 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME]
Once you finish up with that,

00:07:13.850 --> 00:07:15.602 position:50% align:center
you're free to call it a night.

00:07:15.685 --> 00:07:18.355 position:50% align:center
Ah! Thank you very much!

00:07:20.273 --> 00:07:21.983 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME grunts]

00:07:25.236 --> 00:07:29.032 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI] So... what ever
happened with Mr. Yanagida?

00:07:29.115 --> 00:07:30.533 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:07:30.617 --> 00:07:31.951 position:50% align:center
I, uh...

00:07:32.035 --> 00:07:36.373 position:50% align:center
I haven't been
able to contact him.

00:07:36.456 --> 00:07:38.958 position:50% align:center
Ah...

00:07:39.042 --> 00:07:40.960 position:50% align:center
Okay, then I'll call him myself.

00:07:41.044 --> 00:07:42.379 position:50% align:center
Hey!

00:07:42.462 --> 00:07:43.838 position:50% align:center
[OPERATOR 9] The number you
have dialed is currently

00:07:43.922 --> 00:07:46.883 position:50% align:center
unavailable. Please try
your call again later.

00:07:46.966 --> 00:07:48.718 position:50% align:center
Pretty sure that means
he blocked you.

00:07:48.802 --> 00:07:52.097 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO] What? Wow,
that actually hurts.

00:07:52.180 --> 00:07:55.725 position:50% align:center
Seriously? Things are
that bad between you guys?

00:07:55.809 --> 00:07:57.852 position:50% align:center
Well, I thought
things were okay,

00:07:57.936 --> 00:08:01.648 position:50% align:center
which was all thanks
to my colleague, but...

00:08:01.731 --> 00:08:04.567 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI] Hey, tell me
more about that person.

00:08:04.651 --> 00:08:06.069 position:50% align:center
Who is it?

00:08:06.152 --> 00:08:09.906 position:50% align:center
You've mentioned them before,
so now I'm kinda curious.

00:08:09.989 --> 00:08:11.741 position:50% align:center
She really loves
to make clothes,

00:08:11.825 --> 00:08:14.828 position:50% align:center
but people are very against it.

00:08:14.911 --> 00:08:17.414 position:50% align:center
Still, she's worked
incredibly hard.

00:08:17.497 --> 00:08:20.667 position:50% align:center
She's improved a ton
and even made the finals.

00:08:22.168 --> 00:08:24.254 position:50% align:center
So her hard work is paying off!

00:08:24.337 --> 00:08:25.797 position:50% align:center
I guess it's not a myth!

00:08:25.880 --> 00:08:28.758 position:50% align:center
I have no doubt she's out
there doing that right now.

00:08:28.842 --> 00:08:30.385 position:50% align:center
She knows she
won't truly be seen

00:08:30.468 --> 00:08:31.720 position:50% align:center
unless she gives it her all.

00:08:31.803 --> 00:08:33.513 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:08:35.473 --> 00:08:37.142 position:50% align:center
Hey, Ikuto.

00:08:37.225 --> 00:08:40.520 position:50% align:center
The thing about me...
is that more than anything,

00:08:40.603 --> 00:08:43.106 position:50% align:center
I want to prove people wrong.

00:08:43.189 --> 00:08:46.735 position:50% align:center
People like my dad and
this woman named Shizuku.

00:08:46.818 --> 00:08:49.195 position:50% align:center
Is there anyone
like that for you?

00:08:52.699 --> 00:08:56.453 position:50% align:center
Now that you mention it...
Yeah, there is.

00:08:56.536 --> 00:08:58.621 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
Good. Then let's show 'em...

00:08:58.705 --> 00:09:00.290 position:50% align:center
...together!

00:09:00.373 --> 00:09:01.624 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:09:03.293 --> 00:09:05.170 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO]
Yes!

00:09:10.258 --> 00:09:12.677 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO]
No... How did we end up here?

00:09:12.761 --> 00:09:16.139 position:50% align:center
I told you, it's best not to
let a fight drag on like this.

00:09:16.222 --> 00:09:18.308 position:50% align:center
Besides, if you're aren't
on top of your game,

00:09:18.391 --> 00:09:20.393 position:50% align:center
you won't be able to
bring it to the festival.

00:09:20.477 --> 00:09:21.895 position:50% align:center
So get it together.

00:09:21.978 --> 00:09:23.438 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO]
I'm sorry.

00:09:23.521 --> 00:09:26.733 position:50% align:center
--[CHIYUKI] Ikuto, come on!
--[IKUTO] Please don't make me.

00:09:26.816 --> 00:09:28.276 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
Chin up! Don't hunch like that!

00:09:28.360 --> 00:09:30.487 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO] Look, I'm not in
the right headspace for this!

00:09:30.570 --> 00:09:32.489 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI grunts, gasps]

00:09:34.407 --> 00:09:36.868 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:09:36.951 --> 00:09:39.204 position:50% align:center
How do you... both...?

00:09:39.287 --> 00:09:40.413 position:50% align:center
[IKUTO]
Miss Kokoro!

00:09:40.497 --> 00:09:42.540 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry for causing
you so much trouble!

00:09:42.624 --> 00:09:44.834 position:50% align:center
And, uh...

00:09:44.918 --> 00:09:46.544 position:50% align:center
I want to introduce
you to my friend!

00:09:46.628 --> 00:09:49.964 position:50% align:center
This is Miss Chiyuki Fujito.
She'll be modeling for my show.

00:09:50.048 --> 00:09:51.675 position:50% align:center
Ikuto.

00:09:51.758 --> 00:09:53.593 position:50% align:center
This is her.

00:09:53.677 --> 00:09:55.637 position:50% align:center
The amazing model
I told you about before.

00:09:55.720 --> 00:09:57.222 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:09:57.305 --> 00:09:59.557 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
Sorry for barging in like this.

00:09:59.641 --> 00:10:00.975 position:50% align:center
Is Mr. Yanagida here?

00:10:01.059 --> 00:10:04.229 position:50% align:center
[KOKORO grunts] No, he's
actually gone right now.

00:10:04.312 --> 00:10:07.774 position:50% align:center
And I'm afraid I'm heading
out for a shoot, too. Sorry.

00:10:07.857 --> 00:10:08.942 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
I see.

00:10:09.025 --> 00:10:11.403 position:50% align:center
Sounds like you
better get going, then.

00:10:11.486 --> 00:10:13.113 position:50% align:center
Let's come back, Ikuto.

00:10:13.196 --> 00:10:14.698 position:50% align:center
Sorry, again.

00:10:14.781 --> 00:10:15.990 position:50% align:center
--[door closes]
--[footsteps]

00:10:16.074 --> 00:10:17.450 position:50% align:center
[KOKORO]
Mr. Ikuto.

00:10:17.534 --> 00:10:18.493 position:50% align:center
Yes?

00:10:18.576 --> 00:10:20.495 position:50% align:center
I'm happy that you came by.

00:10:20.578 --> 00:10:22.580 position:50% align:center
I'll give you
a call later, okay?

00:10:22.664 --> 00:10:25.792 position:50% align:center
[footsteps]

00:10:28.962 --> 00:10:30.588 position:50% align:center
She really loves
to make clothes,

00:10:30.672 --> 00:10:33.883 position:50% align:center
but people are very against it.

00:10:33.967 --> 00:10:36.428 position:50% align:center
She's worked incredibly hard.

00:10:36.511 --> 00:10:39.764 position:50% align:center
I'm serious about
becoming a real designer!

00:10:41.016 --> 00:10:43.601 position:50% align:center
Are you... good?

00:10:43.685 --> 00:10:45.895 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI] Sorry, Ikuto.
I'm going after her.

00:10:45.979 --> 00:10:48.189 position:50% align:center
Wait, you're what?

00:10:49.232 --> 00:10:53.028 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI] I'm so frustrated.
If you're serious...

00:10:53.111 --> 00:10:57.824 position:50% align:center
If you're serious,
then stand up for yourself!

00:10:57.907 --> 00:11:00.035 position:50% align:center
Just get in the car.

00:11:02.120 --> 00:11:03.705 position:50% align:center
[IGARASHI]
Hey!

00:11:05.540 --> 00:11:08.209 position:50% align:center
May I? It'll only
take one minute.

00:11:08.293 --> 00:11:11.504 position:50% align:center
[grunts] I'm not letting
you get mixed up in this.

00:11:11.588 --> 00:11:14.341 position:50% align:center
I see absolutely
no benefit to it.

00:11:14.424 --> 00:11:16.009 position:50% align:center
You know that your
dressmaking skills

00:11:16.092 --> 00:11:18.720 position:50% align:center
will never surpass your
talent as a model, right?

00:11:18.803 --> 00:11:21.139 position:50% align:center
[CHIYUKI]
Well, here's an idea.

00:11:21.222 --> 00:11:24.392 position:50% align:center
Just give her one shot.
One shot to be a designer.

00:11:24.476 --> 00:11:26.144 position:50% align:center
Why don't you shut it, shrimp?

00:11:26.227 --> 00:11:29.731 position:50% align:center
Look, what you're saying is
not even worth considering.

00:11:29.814 --> 00:11:33.360 position:50% align:center
Tsumura, you actually get to
design and you choose her?

00:11:33.443 --> 00:11:35.445 position:50% align:center
I admit, I'm surprised.

00:11:35.528 --> 00:11:37.447 position:50% align:center
Seems like you're no longer
in need of money, though,

00:11:37.530 --> 00:11:38.615 position:50% align:center
so good for you.

00:11:38.698 --> 00:11:39.616 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:11:39.699 --> 00:11:41.785 position:50% align:center
What? All I did was suggest that

00:11:41.868 --> 00:11:44.120 position:50% align:center
he ask Hasegawa to
